A shanty town

40:15.947 --> 40:19.017
007

40:20.719 --> 40:23.755
007

40:25.257 --> 40:28.326
At ocean eleven

40:29.061 --> 40:32.064
And the rude boys
A go wail

40:33.832 --> 40:37.002
'Cause them out of jail

40:38.770 --> 40:41.807
Rude boys cannot fail

40:43.008 --> 40:45.977
- 'Cause them must get bail
- [Tom groans]

40:46.178 --> 40:48.647
- [radio turns off]
- [Gemma laughs] Tom.

40:51.316 --> 40:53.185
Tom, you okay?

40:55.954 --> 40:57.322
- [Tom grunts]
- Tom!

40:59.758 --> 41:00.725
[Gemma] Are you all right?

41:07.199 --> 41:08.200
Let me see.

41:09.367 --> 41:10.368
[door slams]

41:11.336 --> 41:12.337
Are you okay?

41:25.951 --> 41:27.819
We can't be with you
all the time.

41:29.121 --> 41:30.989
People like to be alone
sometimes, okay?

41:34.359 --> 41:35.360
Do you understand?

41:38.864 --> 41:41.800
Not being with each other
all the time.

41:47.305 --> 41:48.373
Forget it.

41:56.381 --> 41:58.283
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight, Mother.

42:01.219 --> 42:02.387
I'm not your mother.

42:05.891 --> 42:06.892
[door closes]

42:07.893 --> 42:09.161
[screams]

42:11.196 --> 42:12.197
What the fuck?

42:13.498 --> 42:15.367
What do you want? We fed you.

42:16.134 --> 42:18.301
- What do you want?
- [screaming continues]

42:18.303 --> 42:21.673
Jesus! Say what you want.
What do you want?

42:22.474 --> 42:24.442
Shut up. Shut up!

42:25.377 --> 42:27.810
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

42:27.812 --> 42:28.880
[boy stops screaming]

42:30.081 --> 42:32.115
[imitates Tom] Gemma, please,
just let me do this, okay?

42:32.117 --> 42:35.086
This is something I can do, just
please, Gemma, let me do this.

42:35.754 --> 42:36.755
You're fucking disgusting.

42:37.856 --> 42:38.323
[boy imitating Tom]
Please, Gemma, just please.

42:38.823 --> 42:39.791
Do you know that?

42:40.859 --> 42:41.193
[boy imitating Tom]
Just please let me do this.

42:42.427 --> 42:43.126
- This is something I can do...
- You're fucking disgusting!

42:43.128 --> 42:44.062
...please, Gemma, let me do...

42:47.465 --> 42:48.798
[door closes]

42:48.800 --> 42:49.801
[urinating]

42:50.468 --> 42:52.204
[footsteps approaching]

42:53.939 --> 42:55.040
[Tom coughs]

43:08.086 --> 43:09.721
[flushes]

43:45.390 --> 43:46.391
[Tom] Sorry.

43:56.468 --> 43:57.469
[Gemma] It's okay.

44:26.064 --> 44:27.532
[screams]

44:36.508 --> 44:38.943
[imitating Gemma] I am fucking
disgusting, you know that?

44:39.311 --> 44:41.179
I am fucking disgusting.

45:13.679 --> 45:14.946
Are you gonna dig today?

45:16.247 --> 45:18.483
Yeah. Yeah, I guess.

45:20.985 --> 45:22.354
Do you feel like
you're making progress?

45:24.422 --> 45:25.423
Yeah.

45:26.558 --> 45:28.493
Yeah. So, I'm gonna, um...
I'm gonna get back to it.

45:29.094 --> 45:29.994
Thanks.

45:42.708 --> 45:43.642
[door closes]

45:54.552 --> 45:56.020
[Tom grunts]

46:02.628 --> 46:04.963
[creature shrieking in distance]

46:15.340 --> 46:17.175
[creature continues shrieking]

46:22.280 --> 46:23.616
[Tom grunts]

46:33.425 --> 46:34.590
[boy imitating Gemma]
What the fuck!

46:34.592 --> 46:35.726
[Gemma] Go to bed.

46:35.728 --> 46:36.993
[boy imitating Gemma] Go to bed.

46:36.995 --> 46:38.361
[Gemma] Listen to me. Go to bed.

46:38.363 --> 46:39.529
[boy imitating Gemma]
Listen to me,

46:39.531 --> 46:40.530
- go to bed.
- [Gemma] Stop!

46:40.532 --> 46:41.433
[boy imitating Gemma] Stop.

46:42.333 --> 46:46.237
[creature shrieking]

46:50.074 --> 46:51.075
[gasps]

47:01.219 --> 47:03.955
[static]

47:13.598 --> 47:14.532
Gemma.

47:16.769 --> 47:17.636
No.

47:18.604 --> 47:19.603
On.

47:19.605 --> 47:21.005
- No.
- On.

47:21.206 --> 47:22.106
No.

47:28.747 --> 47:30.346
What am I supposed to do
with him?

47:30.348 --> 47:32.618
[static]

47:36.655 --> 47:37.555
Whatever.

47:41.159 --> 47:42.227
[imitates Gemma]
Whatever.

47:43.528 --> 47:49.735
[boy screaming]

47:58.611 --> 47:59.712
[screaming stops]

48:10.723 --> 48:13.322
- What are you doing?
- [boy screaming]

48:13.324 --> 48:15.159
- [boy stops screaming]
- [Gemma] Tom!

48:15.426 --> 48:17.493
- I'm locking it up.
- [boy screaming]

48:17.495 --> 48:18.596
I'm gonna starve it.

48:19.597 --> 48:22.066
- Tom. Tom.
- Gemma, stay!

48:23.736 --> 48:25.169
[boy continues screaming]

48:34.680 --> 48:38.283
All right. Get in. Come on.

48:40.318 --> 48:42.485
- [screaming continues]
- [Gemma] Give me the key.

48:42.487 --> 48:44.153
- No, no. Get back in the house.
- Give me the key!

48:44.155 --> 48:45.789
- Get back in the house!
- Tom. Tom!

48:45.791 --> 48:49.460
- Gemma, come on.
- Tom, give me the key!

48:49.828 --> 48:51.062
[screaming]

48:52.463 --> 48:53.462
[both grunt]

48:53.464 --> 48:55.131
I am not looking after it, okay?

48:55.133 --> 48:56.465
You will leave it there,
don't play with it,

48:56.467 --> 48:58.167
don't feed it, don't have
anything to do with it.

48:58.169 --> 48:59.569
- You will let it starve.
- Let me up!

48:59.571 --> 49:01.672
Look, it has you acting
like you're its fucking mother,

49:01.674 --> 49:03.339
okay, you're... You're putting it
to bed at night,

49:03.341 --> 49:04.507
you're telling it
not to watch cartoons.

49:04.509 --> 49:06.812
- Tom, let me up!
- [both panting]

49:14.185 --> 49:16.154
[both panting]

49:18.289 --> 49:20.626
Look, I'm sorry, but I...
I will not let you help it.

49:21.492 --> 49:24.095
Okay. If they don't want it
to die, they'll come for it.

49:28.199 --> 49:29.200
It's up to them.

49:35.239 --> 49:38.376
[screaming]

49:41.379 --> 49:42.547
What if they don't come?

49:44.315 --> 49:45.381
What are we supposed to do?

49:45.383 --> 49:47.585
Do we just sit here
and we wait for him to die?

49:48.687 --> 49:50.388
- It.
- What?

49:50.756 --> 49:52.791
It. Not him.

49:54.292 --> 49:55.493
Stop saying him.

49:58.797 --> 50:01.299
If it dies,
maybe they'll let us go.

50:15.346 --> 50:16.347
[keys jingling]

50:16.849 --> 50:17.816
[Gemma] Hey.

50:19.350 --> 50:21.250
Hey, it's okay.

50:21.252 --> 50:22.888
He's not gonna hurt you,
I promise.

50:24.389 --> 50:25.390
You can come out.

50:31.630 --> 50:32.631
I'm sorry.

51:00.258 --> 51:02.527
- [Tom grunts]
- [digging]

51:08.701 --> 51:10.301
[pants]

51:16.041 --> 51:17.442
[Tom] Do you hear me?

51:18.376 --> 51:19.444
I can hear you.

51:20.378 --> 51:21.379
Do you hear me?

51:22.681 --> 51:23.682
[Tom coughs]

51:24.616 --> 51:25.617
I can hear you.

51:27.418 --> 51:28.519
[Gemma] He'll get tired soon.

51:30.288 --> 51:31.456
And he'll go to sleep.

51:34.693 --> 51:36.294
You should go to sleep, too.

51:36.995 --> 51:37.996
Have a dream.

51:40.565 --> 51:41.700
What's a dream?

51:44.036 --> 51:45.236
It's, um...

51:47.072 --> 51:51.808
It's like all sorts of moving
pictures in your mind,

51:51.810 --> 51:53.444
but no one else can see them.

51:54.012 --> 51:55.580
I've never had a dream.

51:56.514 --> 51:57.515
Well...

51:59.651 --> 52:00.919
close your eyes and try.

52:11.462 --> 52:12.595
[Tom]
Whoever's on the other side,

52:12.597 --> 52:15.399
can you hear me?
I know you can hear me.

52:18.436 --> 52:19.872
[Tom shouting indistinctly]

52:24.710 --> 52:25.878
Can you hear me?

52:27.445 --> 52:28.847
I know you're out there.

52:44.830 --> 52:45.831
[sighs]

53:02.981 --> 53:03.982
[groans]

53:08.620 --> 53:09.621
[grunts]

53:18.563 --> 53:19.597
[sighs]

53:32.978 --> 53:34.445
[Tom coughs]

53:38.750 --> 53:39.785
[door opens]

54:10.581 --> 54:12.481
[boy] What lovely sky we have.

54:12.483 --> 54:15.051
It is lovely to live
under a lovely sky

54:15.053 --> 54:18.891
and a lovely house with
lovely houses all around us.

54:22.560 --> 54:23.862
You are such a mystery.

54:27.132 --> 54:29.601
You're a mystery
and I'm gonna solve you.

54:31.136 --> 54:33.872
I'm a mystery. I'm a mystery.

54:37.142 --> 54:38.507
Do you see that cloud?

54:38.509 --> 54:40.078
What's that cloud
in the shape of?

54:40.712 --> 54:41.713
[boy] A cloud.

54:42.480 --> 54:43.481
That's right.

54:46.218 --> 54:47.185
Do you see that other cloud?

54:48.787 --> 54:49.719
Yes.

54:49.721 --> 54:51.555
[Gemma] What's that cloud
in the shape of?

54:52.490 --> 54:53.892
- A cloud.
- [Gemma] Yes.

54:54.726 --> 54:56.628
Another cloud-shaped cloud.

54:57.029 --> 54:59.563
All the clouds here
are shaped like clouds.

55:00.132 --> 55:02.566
Perfect, sickening...

55:03.969 --> 55:05.103
little clouds.

55:06.772 --> 55:08.006
Do you like clouds?

55:08.607 --> 55:09.775
Where I come from...

55:11.243 --> 55:13.910
clouds come in all shapes
and sizes,

55:13.912 --> 55:15.979
some of them look like faces

55:15.981 --> 55:18.582
and some of them look
like dogs.

55:19.151 --> 55:20.518
Woof, woof!

55:22.254 --> 55:24.890
[both barking]

55:32.297 --> 55:35.867
[howling]

56:00.058 --> 56:01.559
[cries]

56:06.131 --> 56:07.632
[sniffs]

56:13.972 --> 56:16.675
[crying continues]

56:25.250 --> 56:26.985
- [digging]
- [Tom grunting]

56:38.330 --> 56:39.765
[Tom grunts]

57:49.668 --> 57:50.669
[Tom grunting]

58:11.156 --> 58:12.657
Did you see the boy?

58:13.291 --> 58:14.993
[Tom] No.
[grunts]

58:18.130 --> 58:19.898
- He's gone missing.
- [Tom] Well...

58:20.866 --> 58:22.134
so have we.

58:34.846 --> 58:38.250
- [Gemma] Hello!
- [voice echoes]

58:41.253 --> 58:44.422
- Where are you?
- [voice echoes]

59:06.878 --> 59:07.944
Where did you go?

59:07.946 --> 59:09.781
- [digging]
- [Tom grunts]

01:00:12.344 --> 01:00:13.411
[coughs]

01:00:26.591 --> 01:00:27.892
[static]

01:00:34.532 --> 01:00:35.767
Where were you today?

01:00:36.835 --> 01:00:38.403
I'm solving a mystery.

01:00:39.037 --> 01:00:40.038
[Gemma] Really?

01:00:40.872 --> 01:00:41.973
What did you discover?

01:00:42.307 --> 01:00:43.308
[boy] Lots.

01:00:44.209 --> 01:00:46.411
[Gemma] Lots? Like what?

01:00:47.112 --> 01:00:48.313
[boy] Lots and lots.

01:00:49.581 --> 01:00:51.549
[Gemma] Did you meet anyone when
you were solving the mystery?

01:00:51.950 --> 01:00:53.818
I met you when I was finished.

01:00:57.322 --> 01:00:58.490
Did you meet anyone else?

01:00:59.991 --> 01:01:01.526
Anyone you've never met before?

01:01:06.298 --> 01:01:07.299
Who?

01:01:10.368 --> 01:01:11.870
I'm not allowed to say.

01:01:21.479 --> 01:01:22.480
[button clicks]

01:01:28.987 --> 01:01:29.988
Let's play a game.

01:01:31.456 --> 01:01:32.891
Let's play pretend.

01:01:38.163 --> 01:01:39.164
Pretend to be me.

01:01:41.933 --> 01:01:43.234
[imitating Gemma, sighs]
Whatever.

01:01:43.501 --> 01:01:44.436
[claps]

01:01:45.970 --> 01:01:47.505
Can you pretend to be Tom?

01:01:52.510 --> 01:01:53.845
[Imitating Tom]
Gemma, stay!

01:01:55.380 --> 01:01:56.479
[claps]

01:01:56.481 --> 01:01:58.516
- Will I do a dog?
- Yes, please.

01:01:59.150 --> 01:02:00.251
[barking]

01:02:03.288 --> 01:02:05.290
Is there anyone else you can do?

01:02:09.227 --> 01:02:10.462
Someone you met today?

01:02:13.164 --> 01:02:14.399
Pretend to be that person.

01:02:15.467 --> 01:02:16.468
[takes deep breath]

01:02:24.677 --> 01:02:26.411
[groans]

01:02:30.683 --> 01:02:33.017
[shrieking]

01:02:39.658 --> 01:02:42.394
[gasps, sobs]

01:02:44.295 --> 01:02:47.298
Are you overwhelmed again,
Mother?

01:02:48.566 --> 01:02:50.935
I am not your mother.

01:02:52.705 --> 01:02:54.305
Are you overwhelmed?

01:02:55.407 --> 01:02:59.411
I want... to go home.

01:03:00.044 --> 01:03:01.045
[chuckles]

01:03:01.747 --> 01:03:04.249
Silly Mother, you are home.

01:03:19.597 --> 01:03:20.666
[utensils clattering]

01:03:30.643 --> 01:03:31.644
Thanks.

01:03:32.510 --> 01:03:33.511
You're welcome.

01:03:34.680 --> 01:03:35.681
Do you mean that?

01:03:37.616 --> 01:03:41.319
Or is that sarcasm?
Are you being sarcastic?

01:03:43.221 --> 01:03:44.222
No.

01:03:45.290 --> 01:03:48.026
But you don't really mean
that I'm welcome, right?

01:03:49.227 --> 01:03:50.228
I was being polite.

01:03:51.463 --> 01:03:53.498
[boy]
Why are you being polite?

01:03:56.367 --> 01:03:57.368
Is it fear?

01:04:00.038 --> 01:04:01.039
Probably.

01:04:16.387 --> 01:04:17.388
[imitating Gemma]
Probably.

01:04:25.330 --> 01:04:26.331
[wheezing]

01:04:39.812 --> 01:04:41.246
[knocks]

01:04:43.849 --> 01:04:45.049
[Tom coughing]

01:04:46.484 --> 01:04:47.585
[Tom grunts]

